Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop onto a
large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{},
then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin
strips.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced Chicken Breast{260%g} and sliced pepper to the pan.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir-fry until the peppers have softened and the chicken is golden all over,
~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix together the garlic, @Tomato Puree{30%g},
@North Indian Style Spice Mix{1} and half the @Mango Chutney{80%g}.

Once the chicken is cooked, stir the mixture into the pan until well combined.

Pop the @Plain Taco Tortillas{6} onto a #baking tray{} and into the oven to warm
through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pop the tortillas (3 per person) onto your plates and share out half the
@Mayonnaise{1} in the centre of each one.

Top with the @Wild Rocket{40%g} and mango chutney chicken, then drizzle over
the remaining @Mayonnaise{1} and mango chutney. Fold over one end to encase the
filling and roll up.

Serve with the wedges alongside.

Enjoy!